Var_Description_2020: This variable was created using responses to questions about whether a respondent felt nervous or stressed, calm and peaceful, restless, energetic, and downhearted. The response options to each of these questions are: None of the time (1 point), A little of the time (2 points), Some of the time (3 points), Most of the time (4 points), and All of the time (5 points). We take an average of the point values and multiply that result by 20 in order to get a mental health score between 0 and 100, with respondents with a 0 having a low mental health score and those with a 100 having a high mental health score.

Var_Description_2020: This variable provides a respondents' approximate monthly income. The possible response options are: less than $1,250, $1,250 to $2,499, $2,500 to $4,999, $5,000 to $7,499, $7,500 to $9,999, $10,000 or more, and Don't know. For the Fall 2018-Spring 2019 dataset, these values are provided in both monthly and annual buckets. Then, skip-logic allows the respondent to choose only monthly or annual numbers, based on what they said in this question.
